&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1 Blackburrow -&amp;nbsp; A great zone! One of my all time favorites. Where dungeon crawling was born! But it's still an "outside" zone where SoW and other outdoor spells work. I like that they are sending newbies there on one of the new armor quests, but making it a hot zone would give them reason to stay beyond the requirements for the quest. This zone can accomodate characters from 6 or 7 up to the high teens. There are numerous camp spots and the re-pop rate is nice. I miss the trains....&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2. Runnyeye - as I observed earlier. Can be a problem zone if too crowded. More than one group per level and you are running into mob sharing problems. IMHO LOIO would be a better choice here because of the level spread and the wide open spaces. Good place for kiters to learn their craft. At the very least SOE should remove the negative ZEM for this zone permanently.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3. Frontier Mountains - Giants, wurms etc. who could ask for more?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4 Permafrost - Poor old Lady Vox. Nobody visits her anymore.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;5 Kaesora - Love this zone, but you gotta have a REASON to go back there once you have the drop for the Howling Stones key.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;6 Cazic-Thule - Never been there. Itching to get high enough.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
