      <description>How about an indoor and an outdoor hotspot for each level?  Certain classes, Druids and Rangers come to mind, often find it hard to hunt in the indoor zones while others benefit from them.  If it's possible, maybe a monthly rotation.  With the new tutorial, this would be a great way for people to learn how to get around.  Just a couple of wishes...&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I also think Kedge Keep is a good choice for a new Hotspot (thanks Chantenya).  I was there, both with a group and solo, recently and the place was desserted.  Fair XP and a layout that favors separate group camps.  Eastern Wastes also - good variey of mobs and a couple of nice quests.  Nice wide open spaces also.</description>
