      <description>I am all for the hot spot changes.  I would like to see Echo Caverns knocked out of that book.  Never had a good liking for that area, and I think it was because the zone is just to small.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;My favorite place from 14 to 16 right now is The Warrens.  Usually quiet with a random wandering soul every so often.  Easy spots to pull to and you can easily get to the zone in a pinch.  Front mobs won't agro you even if you sit to meditate.  And like I said begin your level 14 task, and you finish right around the time you ding 16.  The easiest two levels in the new armor tasks.  So if you create new hot spots at least keep The Warrens with an experience bonus.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The loot is good for selling.  Have quite a few named mobs in here and usually I only explore half to two thirds of the zone.  This leaves me another half to third I still have yet to check out, but by that time I am on my way to the next task or doing the evil side task to continue on with my armor quests.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;How about Hollowshade Moor?  My Bard lives in that zone right now hunting Owlbears, Sonic Wolves, and Grimlings and she is only 19.  I love kiting that zone because it has the wide open effect to it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Well those are my ideas, and that is my 1 cp for now.</description>
